@startuml
title Athena JS CLI behavior after help + error normalization

skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam Rectangle {
  BackgroundColor #D9EAD3
  BorderColor #38761D
}
skinparam ArrowColor #355C7D

actor "Developer" as Dev

rectangle "parseCommand(argv)\n--help support for generate/help generate" as Parse #D9EAD3
rectangle "runCLI runtime wrapper\n(error normalization for 3D000)" as CliRuntime #CFE2F3
rectangle "runSchemaGenerator(...)" as Run #E2F0D9
rectangle "bin formatter\nmessage-first output" as Bin #D0E0E3
rectangle "Terminal output" as Output #EAF4EA

Dev --> Parse : athena-js generate --help
Parse --> Output : shows generate usage

Dev --> Parse : athena-js generate --config ...
Parse --> CliRuntime : command accepted
CliRuntime --> Run : execute generator
Run --> CliRuntime : postgres 3D000
CliRuntime --> Bin : normalized actionable message
Bin --> Output : concise failure + next step

note right of Output
Outputs now guide recovery:
- identify missing database
- point to provider.connectionString/provider.database
end note

@enduml
